==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Transubstantiation
<hw>Tran`sub*stan`ti*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>transubstantiatio</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>transsubstantiation</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A change into
another substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(R. C. Theol.)</fld> <def>The doctrine held by Roman
Catholics, that the bread and wine in the Mass is converted into the
body and blood of Christ; -- distinguished from
<contr>consubstantiation</contr>, and
<contr>impanation</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Transubstantiator</ent>⟦br⟧
